  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies a color override for a single entry in a font color palette.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontPaletteOverride` replaces one entry in a font's CPAL color palette with a custom
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor> value. An array of overrides is passed via
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.PaletteOverrides> when cloning a typeface.

The `Color` field stores an `SKColor` value (ARGB, `0xAARRGGBB`).

`SKFontPaletteOverride` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var overrides = new SKFontPaletteOverride[]
{
    new SKFontPaletteOverride { Index = 0, Color = (uint)SKColors.Red },
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    PaletteIndex = 0,
    PaletteOverrides = overrides,
};
using var typeface = originalTypeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
